:JO_Initial_Coin_Offering a :Scene;
  rdf:value """
    The goal of this step is to execute a carefully planned ICO. Key deliverables will include the tokenomics, whitepaper, fundraising strategy, marketing, PR, legal compliance, exchange listings and token sale website.


    Tasks:
        1. Finalize the tokenomics model and create a whitepaper for the ICO
        2. Develop a comprehensive fundraising strategy and a detailed marketing plan
        3. Craft and distribute press releases and public relations materials to generate buzz and interest in the project
        4. Ensure full regulatory compliance with all applicable laws and regulations
        5. Establish relationships with reputable cryptocurrency exchanges to list the token after the sale
        6. Design and develop a user-friendly and secure token sale website
    """;
  :label "Initial Coin Offering (ICO) Preparation";
  :url "/ux/ai";
  :comment """
    JO begins to plan and prepare for the Initial Coin Offering, ensuring a well-structured and successful launch.
    The DAO will play a crucial role in guiding this process.
    """;
  :image "/art/JO.png";
  iq:ai llm:llama-iq;
  iq:to :JO_DAO_Duties .

:JO_DAO_Duties a :Kink;
  rdf:value """
    As part of the DAO's responsibilities, key duties will include:


    1. Smart Contract Maintenance and Upgrades - The DAO will oversee the smart contracts used during the ICO and continue to make necessary changes to ensure maximum efficiency and security.

    2. Treasury and Financial Management - The DAO will be responsible for managing the funds collected during the ICO and ensuring these are allocated efficiently and according to the project's overall plan.

    3. Security - The DAO will continuously monitor security threats to protect the participants from every potential danger such as fraud and theft.

    4. Partnership Management - Aiding in negotiations and execution of business partnerships, aiming to expand our reach and also attract top talent.

    5. User Support and Conflict Resolution - Establishment of multiple streams for clear and flexible user communication regarding what they need. Clear, scalable documentation processes designed to reduce bureaucratic obstacles and escalating issues.
    """;
  :label "DAO Governance and Duties for ICO";
  :url "/ux/ai";
  :comment """
    The DAO will manage and govern the ICO process, ensuring transparency, security, and efficiency.
    JO will work closely with the DAO to ensure a seamless execution of the ICO.
    """;
  :image "/art/JO.png";
  iq:ai llm:llama-iq;
  iq:to :JO_Tokenomics .

:JO_Tokenomics a :Scene;
  rdf:value """
    The tokenomics for this project involves various key facets including:


    -Token supply - capped at 10 billion;
    -Token reserves -  for developers will be set aside to reward achievements within our mission;
    -Community access tools - a mobile app will be released containing tools to further assist token holders


    This will allow users to fully understand the token distribution mechanism and explore future strategy options.
